/*
 * Compute the ReLU function on every element of x. Elements less than zero become zero,
 * while elements greater than zero stay the same.
 *
 * The implementation uses an explicit parallel loop with a static schedule to exploit
 * intra‑array data parallelism on x86‑64.  The comparison and conditional store are
 * performed in a single branchless operation to keep the code vectorisable and
 * to avoid the per‑element functor allocation introduced by std::transform.
